---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Trust and Safety | Property App 2026" description="How Property App protects buyers, renters, owners, and listing quality.">
  <section class="hero-shell glass-card">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <span class="pill">Trust and safety</span>
      <h1>Trust needs system design, moderation, and visible protection.</h1>
      <p>
        Property marketplaces fail when listings are noisy, contact pathways are opaque, and users are pushed into rushed decisions. We are building the protection layer directly into search, enquiry, verification, reporting, and account workflows.
      </p>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <span>Structured enquiries instead of contact scraping</span>
        <span>Verification pathways for owner credibility</span>
        <span>Listing reports and moderation visibility</span>
        <span>Shortlist, compare, and trust context before commitment</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid section-space">
    <article class="glass-card content-card">
      <strong>For buyers and renters</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Verified-owner signals appear where identity or ownership status has been reviewed.</li>
        <li>Structured enquiries reduce the need to hand over information blindly.</li>
        <li>Shortlist, compare, and affordability tools slow down rushed decisions.</li>
        <li>Listing reporting exists for suspicious, inaccurate, or duplicated inventory.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="glass-card content-card">
      <strong>For owners and landlords</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Verification request flow sits inside the owner workspace, not outside it.</li>
        <li>Owner-side enquiry tracking, response states, and notes keep leads accountable.</li>
        <li>Time-bounded visibility reduces stale inventory and protects credible supply.</li>
        <li>Photo, location, and trust guidance come before promotion is encouraged.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="glass-card section-shell section-space">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="pill">Security principles</span>
      <h2>Security is not a separate feature. It shapes the product.</h2>
      <p>
        We are designing around protected account access, moderated listing quality, structured user actions, and clearer signals before money or contact details move. The goal is a marketplace that feels safer because the workflows are safer.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="principles-grid">
      <article class="surface-card">
        <strong>Protected account flows</strong>
        <span>Buyer, owner, and admin actions sit behind role-aware account controls instead of ad hoc access paths.</span>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <strong>Moderated trust signals</strong>
        <span>Verification and reporting are operational workflows, not decorative badges.</span>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <strong>Decision support before contact</strong>
        <span>Shortlist, compare, collections, and trust context help users decide before they commit.</span>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <strong>Clear owner accountability</strong>
        <span>Owners manage galleries, response states, listing quality, and visibility in one accountable workspace.</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="glass-card content-card section-space">
    <strong>Practical safety checklist</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not send deposits before identity, viewing conditions, and listing credibility are clear.</li>
      <li>Use shortlist and compare before contacting if you are not yet sure which listing is strongest.</li>
      <li>Report listings that look duplicated, misleading, or suspicious.</li>
      <li>Owners should keep gallery quality, contact details, and listing status current.</li>
      <li>Auction inventory should always include terms, timeline, and registration conditions before serious buyer engagement.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid section-space">
    <a class="glass-card cta-card" href="/about">
      <span class="pill">About us</span>
      <strong>Understand what we are building and why</strong>
      <p>Read the company view behind the product, the market problem we care about, and the standard we are trying to raise.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="glass-card cta-card" href="/why-property-app">
      <span class="pill">Why us</span>
      <strong>See what should make this better than the usual portal</strong>
      <p>Our difference is not just more listings. It is clearer workflows, better decision support, and stronger trust signals.</p>
    </a>
  </section>

  <style is:inline>
    .hero-shell,
    .section-shell,
    .content-card,
    .cta-card {
      padding: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .hero-shell {
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent), transparent 26rem),
        linear-gradient(180deg, color-mix(in srgb, var(--card) 94%, transparent), color-mix(in srgb, var(--card) 82%, transparent));
    }

    .hero-copy,
    .section-head,
    .section-shell,
    .content-card,
    .cta-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-m);
    }

    .hero-copy h1,
    .section-head h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: var(--text-5xl);
      line-height: 0.94;
      letter-spacing: -0.06em;
      max-width: 13ch;
    }

    .hero-copy p,
    .content-card li,
    .section-head p,
    .principles-grid span,
    .cta-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .signal-row,
    .split-grid,
    .principles-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-m);
    }

    .signal-row {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .signal-row span,
    .surface-card {
      padding: var(--space-l);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--card) 78%, transparent);
    }

    .signal-row span {
      font-size: var(--text-sm);
      color: var(--muted);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .split-grid,
    .principles-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .surface-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }

    .content-card ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: var(--space-m);
      display: grid;
      gap: var(--space-xs);
    }

    .content-card strong,
    .surface-card strong,
    .cta-card strong {
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .cta-card {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: inherit;
    }

    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .signal-row,
      .split-grid,
      .principles-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
